msgctxt "sn56.50:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.50:0.2"
msgid "5. Papātavagga "
msgstr "5. A Cliff "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 50. Dutiyasinerupabbatarājasutta → dutiyasinerusuttaṃ (bj) | sineru 2 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn56.50:0.3"
msgid "50. Dutiyasinerupabbatarājasutta "
msgstr "50. Sineru, King of Mountains (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.459, sc1
msgctxt "sn56.50:1.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, sinerupabbatarājāyaṃ parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ gaccheyya, ṭhapetvā satta muggamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, suppose Sineru, the king of mountains, was worn away and eroded except for seven pebbles the size of mustard seeds. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.50:1.2"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn56.50:1.3"
msgid "katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ—yaṃ vā sinerussa pabbatarājassa parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādinnaṃ, yā vā satta muggamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā avasiṭṭhā”ti? "
msgstr "Which is more: the portion of Sineru, the king of mountains, that has been worn away and eroded? Or the seven pebbles the size of mustard seeds that are left?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.50:1.4"
msgid "“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ sinerussa pabbatarājassa yadidaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādinnaṃ; "
msgstr "“Sir, the portion of Sineru, the king of mountains, that has been worn away and eroded is certainly more. "

msgctxt "sn56.50:1.5"
msgid "appamattikā satta muggamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā avasiṭṭhā. "
msgstr "The seven pebbles the size of mustard seeds are tiny. "

msgctxt "sn56.50:1.6"
msgid "Saṅkhampi na upenti, upanidhampi na upenti, kalabhāgampi na upenti sinerussa pabbatarājassa parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādinnaṃ upanidhāya satta muggamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā avasiṭṭhā”ti. "
msgstr "Compared to Sineru, they can’t be reckoned or compared, they’re not even a fraction.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.50:1.7"
msgid "“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa diṭṭhisampannassa puggalassa abhisametāvino etadeva bahutaraṃ dukkhaṃ yadidaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādinnaṃ; appamattakaṃ avasiṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr "“In the same way, for a person with comprehension, a noble disciple accomplished in view, the suffering that’s over and done with is more, what’s left is tiny. "

msgctxt "sn56.50:1.8"
msgid "Saṅkhampi na upeti, upanidhampi na upeti, kalabhāgampi na upeti, purimaṃ dukkhakkhandhaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādinnaṃ upanidhāya yadidaṃ sattakkhattuparamatā; "
msgstr "Compared to the mass of suffering in the past that’s over and done with, it can’t be reckoned or compared, it’s not even a fraction, since there are at most seven more lives. "

msgctxt "sn56.50:1.9"
msgid "yo ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti. "
msgstr "Such a person truly understands about suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn56.50:2.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti. "
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.50:2.2"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.50:2.3"
msgid "Papātavaggo pañcamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn56.50:3.1"
msgid "Cintā papāto pariḷāho, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn56.50:3.2"
msgid "kūṭaṃ vālandhakāro ca; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn56.50:3.3"
msgid "Chiggaḷena ca dve vuttā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn56.50:3.4"
msgid "sineru apare duveti. "
msgstr ""

